MuscleWiki API: This developer-focused service provides access to over 1,900+ exercises mapped to 7,500+ high-quality video demonstrations. It covers 45 distinct muscle groups and includes clear execution steps, complete JSON responses, and a free tier option.Your Move (ymove.app): Built specifically for clean front-end application integration, this REST API bundles 1,021+ standardized HD video demonstrations with adaptive HLS video streaming. It allows you to query movements by difficulty, muscle group, or equipment type.ExerciseLibrary.com API: A scalable REST API hosting over 738+ exercises mapped directly to step-by-step metadata. It links directly to organized YouTube URLs on its free access plan and switches to high-speed CDN-hosted video endpoints on its premium tier.ExerciseDB (RapidAPI): One of the largest available open-source structured text datasets on GitHub, tracking over 11,000+ movements mapping instructions, targets, and attached media assets (often using standard video links or loopable formatting).

If you prefer downloading a static data file directly into your application instead of fetching a third-party server, look for the open-source Exercises-Dataset on GitHub. It provides a clean JSON format indexing 1,324 movements packed with loopable visual demonstrations, targeted equipment, and translation metadata ready to drop straight into your workspace codebase.